# Refinements requirement

When you make substantive changes to the project (code, assets, or documentation), you MUST also update `refinements-changes.md` with a short entry describing:
- What changed (file names or feature area)
- Why it changed (decision/scope shift/rationale)
- When it happened (Day 1/2/3 or date)

# Practical checklist
- After editing files, add a matching bullet under the appropriate section in `refinements-changes.md` before committing.
- If the change log entry is not created, do not proceed with the commit/push.

